premise_source_doc_sentence: When used to refer to the rebroadcast of a single episode , Lucille Ball and Desi Arnaz are generally credited as the inventors of the rerun ; it was first utilized for the American television series I Love Lucy  (  1951 -- 57  )  during Ball 's pregnancy .
A `` Repeat '' is a single episode of a series that is broadcast outside its original timeslot on the same channel/network .
In the United Kingdom , the word `` repeat '' refers only to a single episode ; `` rerun '' or `` rerunning '' is the preferred term for an entire series/season .
The episode is usually the `` repeat '' of the scheduled episode that was broadcast in the original timeslot earlier the previous week .
